1.sl_source: Nočem bonbona, pusti me na miru.
1.en_source: I don't want any candy! Leave me alone.
1.sl_trans: Nočem nobene sladkarije! Pustite me pri miru.

3.sl_source: Kaj vse je storila, mi pa njej nič.
3.en_source: He did all of this and we did nothing to him.
3.sl_trans: Vse to je storil, mi pa mu nismo storili ničesar.

6.sl_source: V komandnem centru ni nobenih sporočil, ker je vojska blokirala vse medije z vsemi podatki.
6.en_source: Here at Command Center in New Jersey there is no new information to report, because the military has clamped a total media blackout on whatever is going on out here.
6.sl_trans: V poveljniškem centru v New Jerseyju ni novih informacij, saj je vojska popolnoma zaprla medije za vse, kar se tu dogaja.

7.sl_source: Uradni predstavniki na temo ne povejo nič novega o pošasti.
7.en_source: Officials are not saying anything about their attempts to contain or control this creature.
7.sl_trans: Uradniki ne povedo ničesar o svojih poskusih, da bi to bitje zajezili ali nadzorovali.

8.en_source: Okay, the situation is under control !

13.en_source: Can I help you, young man?

14.sl_source: Imate kakšne teste za nosečnost, za domačo uporabo?
14.en_source: Do you have any at-home pregnancy tests?
14.sl_trans: Ali imate kakšne domače teste nosečnosti?

15.sl_source: Posebej takšne, ki temeljijo na gonadotrofičnih hormonih... ali clomiphenovem citratu?
15.en_source: Especially ones that look for gonadotrophic hormones... or clomiphene citrate?
15.sl_trans: Še posebej tiste, ki iščejo gonadotrofne hormone... ali klomifen citrat?

31.sl_source: Pustila si me brez klica, pisma, nič do sedaj.
31.en_source: Well, you left without a phone call, letter, nothing, all this time.
31.sl_trans: V vsem tem času ste odšli brez telefonskega klica, pisma, ničesar.

32.sl_source: Mislim, da sem še jezen, da.
32.en_source: Yeah, I guess I am still a little mad.
32.sl_trans: Ja, mislim, da sem še vedno malo jezen.

36.sl_source: Žal mi je, da tako misliš.
36.en_source: I'm sorry you feel that way.
36.sl_trans: Žal mi je, da se tako počutite.

38.en_source: Eight years is a long time.

39.en_source: Can I make you a cup of tea?
39.sl_trans: Ali vam lahko pripravim skodelico čaja?

42.sl_source: Kako lahko gre zapriseženi "zeleni" v službo v zavod za nadzor jedrskih poskusov?
42.en_source: How does a guy go from anti-nuke activist to working for the Nuclear Regulatory Commission?
42.sl_trans: Kako se človek od aktivista proti jedrski elektrarni prelevi v uslužbenca Komisije za jedrsko regulacijo?

43.sl_source: Ko sva na fakulteti skupaj hodila na shode, sva skupaj izoblikovala zavedanje.
43.en_source: When you and I went to rallies together in college we helped to create awareness.
43.sl_trans: Ko sva na fakulteti skupaj hodila na shode, sva pomagala ozaveščati.

44.sl_source: Toda sedaj, v centru dogajanja lahko povzročim pravo spremembo.
44.en_source: But now, from the inside... I'm able to effect real change.
44.sl_trans: Toda zdaj, od znotraj... lahko dosežem resnične spremembe.

45.en_source: And exactly what changes are you trying to effect?

46.en_source: I'm preparing a census for the government.

47.sl_source: Delam katalog novih vrst, posledic jedrskih poskusov.
47.en_source: I'm cataloging new species created as a result of nuclear contamination.
47.sl_trans: Popisujem nove vrste, ki so nastale zaradi jedrskega onesnaženja.

48.en_source: Is that what you think created this?
48.sl_trans: Ali menite, da je to vzrok za nastanek tega?

50.en_source: I found a blood sample earlier.

51.sl_source: Kako blizu pošasti si že bil?
51.en_source: How close did you get to the thing?

53.en_source: What else did you find out?

54.en_source: We know he eats tons of fish.

59.sl_source: Očitno ti testi niso najbolj primerni..- a temeljijo na istih hormonih, ki kažejo nosečnost.
59.en_source: Obviously these tests weren't designed for this... but fundamentally they look for the same hormonal patterns to indicate pregnancy.
59.sl_trans: Ti testi seveda niso bili zasnovani za to, vendar v osnovi iščejo iste hormonske vzorce, ki kažejo na nosečnost.

61.sl_source: Če je prva v svoji vrsti, kako je lahko noseča?
61.en_source: It he's the first of his kind, how can he be pregnant?
61.sl_trans: Če je prvi svoje vrste, kako je lahko noseč?

65.sl_source: Razmišljal sem, zakaj bi prišla tako daleč?
65.en_source: I kept thinking, why would he travel so tar?
65.sl_trans: Ves čas sem razmišljal, zakaj bi potoval tako dehteče?

67.sl_source: Veliko živali potuje daleč za oploditev.
67.en_source: Lots of animals travel great distances for reproduction.
67.sl_trans: Veliko živali prepotuje velike razdalje, da bi se razmnoževale.

68.en_source: That's what he's doing in New York.

72.sl_source: Se zavedaš, da lahko kuščar izleže... 12 jajc naenkrat?
72.en_source: Do you realize that a lizard can lay... up to 12 eggs at a time?
72.sl_trans: Ali se zavedate, da lahko kuščar odloži... do 12 jajc naenkrat?

75.sl_source: To moram nesti v laboratorij, da lahko to vse potrdim.
75.en_source: I have to get this to the lab and see it I can confirm all this.
75.sl_trans: To moram dati v laboratorij in preveriti, ali lahko vse to potrdim.

79.en_source: I'm telling you, man, I heard something.
79.sl_trans: Pravim ti, človek, nekaj sem slišal.

85.sl_source: Zaradi tega vsi kraljevi konji in možje ne bodo zmožni postaviti "velikega jabolka" skupaj.
85.en_source: This is why, in this case, all the king's horses and all the king's men... may not be able to put the Big Apple together again.
85.sl_trans: Zato v tem primeru vsi kraljevi konji in vsi kraljevi možje morda ne bodo mogli ponovno sestaviti Velikega jabolka.

92.en_source: I should've worn my hair back.
92.sl_trans: Morala bi si lase nositi nazaj.

96.sl_source: Kako si prišla do tega posnetka?
96.en_source: How did you get ahold of this material?
96.sl_trans: Kako ste prišli do tega gradiva?

106.sl_source: Imam ekskluzivne posnetke ostalih napadenih področij.
106.en_source: I've got exclusive footage of other places this thing has attacked.
106.sl_trans: Imam ekskluzivne posnetke drugih krajev, ki jih je ta stvar napadla.

110.sl_source: Če bi jo lahko privabili na odprto, npr. Central Park-..
110.en_source: If we can lure him into a more open area such as this portion of Central Park...
110.sl_trans: Če ga lahko zvabimo na bolj odprto območje, kot je ta del Centralnega parka...

111.en_source: I think we can take him down.

112.en_source: Last time you didn't even scratch it.

114.sl_source: Naš "mož črvov", dr. Tatopoulos, je našel kri.
114.en_source: Our worm guy, I mean Dr. Tatopoulos, has found blood.
114.sl_trans: Naš črv, torej doktor Tatopulos, je našel kri.

116.sl_source: Moramo jo spraviti na odprt teren... in uporabiti orožje, ki ne temelji na toplotnem zaznavanju.
116.en_source: We need to get him out into open terrain... and use weapons that don't rely on heat-seeking technology--
116.sl_trans: Spraviti ga moramo na odprt teren in uporabiti orožje, ki ne temelji na tehnologiji iskanja toplote...

118.en_source: I think this situation has become more complicated than that.
118.sl_trans: Mislim, da je situacija postala bolj zapletena kot to.

119.sl_source: V krvi, ki sem jo našel... so sledi, da je pošast tik pred izlegom jajc.
119.en_source: The blood that I collected... revealed that the creature is either about to lay eggs or already has.
119.sl_trans: Kri, ki sem jo zbral, je razkrila, da je bitje tik pred tem, da odloži jajca, ali pa jih je že odložilo.

120.sl_source: Praviš, da je nekje zunaj še kakšna taka pošast?
120.en_source: Are you trying to tell us that there's another one of those things out there?
120.sl_trans: Ali nam želite povedati, da obstaja še ena takšna stvar?

124.en_source: Then how can it be pregnant?

125.en_source: What is this, the virgin lizard?

129.sl_source: Drugače bo rojen nov ducat... vsi pa bodo spet lahko nesli jajca.
129.en_source: Otherwise up to a dozen are going to be born... each one capable of laying eggs on its own.
129.sl_trans: V nasprotnem primeru se jih bo rodilo do ducat... vsaka od njih lahko sama odloži jajca.

130.sl_source: Zelo kmalu bi lahko prišlo do velikega števila pošasti.
130.en_source: Very quickly we could be looking at an enormous population.
130.sl_trans: Zelo hitro bi se lahko zgodilo, da bi imeli ogromno prebivalcev.

131.sl_source: Ko ubijemo pošast, bomo iskali gnezdo.
131.en_source: After we kill the creature, then we'll search for the nest.
131.sl_trans: Ko bomo ubili bitje, bomo poiskali gnezdo.

132.en_source: I think it might be too late by then.
132.sl_trans: Mislim, da bo takrat morda že prepozno.

133.en_source: These eggs will hatch very quickly.
133.sl_trans: Ta jajca se izležejo zelo hitro.

135.sl_source: Zaradi rib, ki smo jih našli v podzemni.
135.en_source: The fish that we found on the subway.
135.sl_trans: Riba, ki smo jo našli na podzemni železnici.

136.en_source: He's not collecting all this food just for himself.
136.sl_trans: Vse te hrane ne zbira samo zase.

137.en_source: He's preparing to feed his young.

138.sl_source: Ostanite z nami do naslednjih novic.
138.en_source: Stay tuned for our special report.

141.en_source: They just promo-ed your spot. It's up right after this.
141.sl_trans: Pravkar so promovirali vaše mesto. Na sporedu je takoj za tem.

143.en_source: Can you turn it up, please?

144.sl_source: Če ima dr. Tatopoulos prav, potem moramo reagirati hitro.
144.en_source: If Dr. Tatopoulos is right, we must act quickly before this problem escalates.
144.sl_trans: Če ima Dr. Tatopoulos prav, moramo ukrepati hitro, preden se ta težava še poveča.

145.sl_source: Bi rad razdelil naše moči, le na podlagi ene teorije?
145.en_source: So you want to divide our efforts based solely on some wild theory?
145.sl_trans: Torej želite razdeliti naša prizadevanja zgolj na podlagi neke divje teorije?

146.sl_source: Nick je imel prav že prej.
146.en_source: Sir, Nick's come through for us before.
146.sl_trans: Sir, Nick nam je pomagal že prej.

149.sl_source: Pošasti niste mogli preprečiti prihoda na Manhattan.
149.en_source: You weren't even able to keep this thing from coming to Manhattan.
149.sl_trans: Niti niste mogli preprečiti, da bi ta stvar prišla na Manhattan.

150.sl_source: Gospodje, oprostite, a to bi morali videti.
150.en_source: Excuse me, gentlemen, but I think we should see this.
150.sl_trans: Oprostite, gospodje, ampak mislim, da bi si morali to ogledati.

151.sl_source: Poglejte si motivacijo najnovejšega nezaželjenega ljubimca.
151.en_source: Look at the methods and motivations of Manhattan's newest unwanted pest.
151.sl_trans: Oglejte si metode in motive najnovejšega neželenega škodljivca na Manhattnu.

153.en_source: That's what Japanese sailors called him in song.
153.sl_trans: Tako so ga v pesmi imenovali japonski mornarji.

154.sl_source: Morski zmaj, ki jim polni srca s strahom.
154.en_source: A mythological sea dragon who filled their hearts with fear.
154.sl_trans: Mitološki morski zmaj, ki je v njihovih srcih vzbujal strah.

157.en_source: That myth has become reality, our modern-day terror. I don't believe it!
157.sl_trans: Ta mit je postal resničnost, naša sodobna groza. Ne verjamem!

161.sl_trans: In to je Gojira, ti bedak!

162.sl_source: Kaže se pot od Manhattan do francoske Polinezije, kjer že več kot 20 let izvajajo jedrske poskuse -
162.en_source: A direct path can be traced from Manhattan to French Polynesia... where nuclear tests have been going on for more than two decades.
162.sl_trans: Od Manhattna do Francoske Polinezije, kjer že več kot dve desetletji potekajo jedrski poskusi, vodi neposredna pot.

163.sl_source: Član raziskovalne skupine dr. Nick Papadopoulus verjame, da pošast dela gnezdo..- in da bo Manhattan začetna točka razvoja nove vrste.
163.en_source: Research team member Dr. Nick Papadopoulus believes.... the creature may be nesting... using Manhattan as ground zero to cultivate the species.
163.sl_trans: Dr. Nick Papadopoulus, član raziskovalne ekipe, verjame...., da se bitje morda gnezdi na Manhattnu, kjer bi lahko gojili to vrsto.

164.sl_source: Združenim močem ameriške vojske... ni uspelo--
164.en_source: This despite the fact that the combined might... of the United States military has been unable to subdue--
164.sl_trans: In to kljub temu, da združena moč... vojske Združenih držav Amerike ni mogla obvladati...

165.en_source: You went to the press with this?
165.sl_trans: S tem ste se obrnili na novinarje?

170.en_source: No, I didn't give them the tape.

171.en_source: It's in my tent right now.

174.en_source: You're officially off this project as of now!
174.sl_trans: S tem projektom ste uradno zaključili!

177.sl_source: Samo naj Hicks najde gnezdo, preden bo prepozno.
177.en_source: Make sure that Hicks finds that nest before it's too late.
177.sl_trans: Poskrbite, da Hicks najde gnezdo, preden bo prepozno.

180.sl_source: Še pred sekundo je bil na drugi liniji.
180.en_source: A second ago you told me he was on the other line. Please.
180.sl_trans: Pred sekundo ste mi rekli, da je na drugi liniji. Prosim.

182.en_source: I really need to talk to him.
182.sl_trans: Resnično se moram pogovoriti z njim.

188.sl_source: Kaj si pa mislila, da se bo zgodilo?
188.en_source: What did you think was going to happen?
188.sl_trans: Kaj ste mislili, da se bo zgodilo?

189.sl_source: Nikoli nisi rekel, da ni za objavo.
189.en_source: You never said it was off the record.
189.sl_trans: Nikoli niste rekli, da je bilo to zunaj zapisnika.

191.en_source: You were supposed to be my friend.

196.sl_source: Ko sva prekinila in ko sem prvič prišla v New York,... sem bila prepričana, da mi bo uspelo.
196.en_source: When we broke up, and I first came out to New York... I was so sure I'd make it.
196.sl_trans: Ko sva se razšla in sem prvič prišla v New York... sem bila tako prepričana, da mi bo uspelo.

198.en_source: That's why I needed the story so bad.
198.sl_trans: Zato sem tako zelo potreboval zgodbo.

199.sl_source: Nisem ti mogla povedati, da sem zguba-
199.en_source: I couldn't tell you I'm a failure.
199.sl_trans: Ne morem vam reči, da sem neuspešen.

200.sl_source: Mislila si, da bo to opravičilo krajo moje kasete?
200.en_source: And you thought that made it okay to steal my tapes?
200.sl_trans: In ste mislili, da zaradi tega ni nič narobe, če ste mi ukradli kasete?

201.en_source: It was a terrible thing to do.

203.sl_source: Vso srečo pri tvoji novi karieri.
203.en_source: Good luck with your new career.

204.sl_source: Mislim, da imaš to, kar rabiš.
204.en_source: I really think you have what it takes.
204.sl_trans: Resnično mislim, da imaš vse, kar potrebuješ.

207.en_source: Yo! Give her a break, will ya?

208.sl_source: Je to najboljša pot do letališča?
208.en_source: Excuse me, is this the best way to the airport?
208.sl_trans: Ali je to najboljša pot do letališča?

214.en_source: I'm afraid I can't do that.
214.sl_trans: Bojim se, da tega ne morem storiti.

216.sl_trans: Ja, vi ste tisti, ki se ukvarja z zavarovalništvom.

221.sl_source: Vaši ameriški prijatelji ne iščejo gnezda.
221.en_source: Your American friends have decided not to look for the creature's nest.
221.sl_trans: Vaši ameriški prijatelji so se odločili, da ne bodo iskali gnezda tega bitja.

227.sl_source: Najprej me ugrabite, potem pa vam naj zaupam?
227.en_source: You hijack me and you expect me to trust you?
227.sl_trans: Ugrabili ste me in pričakujete, da vam bom zaupal?

230.sl_source: Ker samo vi hočete najti gnezdo, tako kot mi.
230.en_source: Because you are the only one who wants to find the nest as much as I do.
230.sl_trans: Ker ste edini, ki si tako kot jaz želite najti gnezdo.

231.sl_source: Kako ste vse to spravili v našo državo?
231.en_source: How did you get all this stuff into the country?
231.sl_trans: Kako ste vse te stvari spravili v državo?

236.sl_source: Ne smem govoriti o teh zadevah.
236.en_source: I'm not permitted to speak of such things.
236.sl_trans: O takih stvareh ne smem govoriti.

237.en_source: You said you needed my trust.
237.sl_trans: Rekel si, da potrebuješ moje zaupanje.

243.sl_source: Moja dolžnost je varovati mojo državo.
243.en_source: It is my job to protect my country.
243.sl_trans: Moja naloga je zaščititi svojo državo.

244.sl_source: Včasih celo pred njo samo,... pred našimi napakami.
244.en_source: Sometimes I must even protect it from itself... from mistakes we've made.
244.sl_trans: Včasih ga moram celo zaščititi pred njim samim... pred napakami, ki smo jih naredili.

245.sl_source: Napake, ki morajo ostati prikrite svetu.
245.en_source: Mistakes we don't want the world to know about.
245.sl_trans: Napake, za katere ne želimo, da bi svet zanje izvedel.

246.en_source: The nuclear tests in the Pacific?

248.en_source: This testing done by my country left a terrible mess.
248.sl_trans: Testiranje, ki ga je opravila moja država, je pustilo strašno zmešnjavo.

249.en_source: We're here to clean it up.

250.en_source: We know how to get into the city.

251.sl_source: Ne vemo, kje naj začnemo iskati.
251.en_source: We just don't know where to start looking.
251.sl_trans: Samo ne vemo, kje naj začnemo iskati.

253.en_source: This is the 23rd Street subway station.
253.sl_trans: To je postaja podzemne železnice na 23. ulici.

254.en_source: That's where we first found the fish.

255.en_source: That'd be a good place to start.

258.sl_source: Vedno sem hotel k francoski tujski legiji.
258.en_source: I always wanted to join the French Foreign Legion.
258.sl_trans: Vedno sem se želel pridružiti francoski tujski legiji.

267.sl_source: Nisem jih mogla pustiti na ulici.
267.en_source: I couldn't just let them sleep on the street.
267.sl_trans: Nisem jih mogel pustiti spati na ulici.

269.sl_source: V sobi se joče zaradi tebe.
269.en_source: In the bedroom crying her eyes out because of you.

271.sl_source: Polnil si ji glavo z "grobo osebo".
271.en_source: That "you gotta be vicious" stuff you tilled her head with.
271.sl_trans: Tisto "moraš biti zloben", s čimer si ji razkuril glavo.

273.en_source: Go talk to her right now.

276.sl_source: Tako kot v prejšnjih novicah-.- nimamo nobenih podatkov, ki bi potrjevali,..- da so nekje jajca.
276.en_source: Contrary to frivolous reporting... we have absolutely no information whatsoever to make us believe... that there are any eggs of the creature in the city.
276.sl_trans: V nasprotju z lahkomiselnim poročanjem... nimamo popolnoma nobenih informacij, ki bi nas prepričale, da so v mestu kakršnakoli jajca tega bitja.

278.en_source: Repeat. There's no reason to panic.

284.en_source: I don't do stuff like this.

287.sl_source: Uničila sem prijateljstvo z moškim, ki se edini briga zame.
287.en_source: Well, I totally screwed up with the only man who will ever care about me.
287.sl_trans: Popolnoma sem pokvarila razmerje z edinim moškim, ki mu je bilo kdaj mar zame.

288.sl_source: Če bi lahko vse popravila, bi to storila?
288.en_source: If I told you you could make it all up, would you?
288.sl_trans: Če bi vam rekel, da si lahko vse to izmislite, ali bi to storili?

291.sl_source: Ko te je pustil na ulici, sem mu sledil.
291.en_source: After he left you in the street, I kinda followed him.
291.sl_trans: Ko te je pustil na ulici, sem mu nekako sledil.

292.sl_source: Hotel sem mu pihati na dušo.
292.en_source: Figured I'd talk some sense into the guy, you know?
292.sl_trans: Pomislil sem, da bi mu lahko vlil nekaj razuma v glavo, kajne?

293.sl_source: Kasneje je zavil v skladišče,... kjer so bili ti francoski gumpci.
293.en_source: Next thing I know, he pulls into this warehouse... with all these French wackos in military outfits.
293.sl_trans: Nato se pripelje v skladišče z vsemi temi francoskimi norci v vojaških oblekah.

294.sl_source: Hočejo se splaziti nazaj v mesto.
294.en_source: They want to sneak back into the city tonight.
294.sl_trans: Danes zvečer se želijo prikrasti nazaj v mesto.

296.sl_source: Če ga bo našel, potem moraš ti poročati o tem,... da je imel vseskozi prav.
296.en_source: If he finds it, I think you should be the one that lets the world know... that this guy was right all along.
296.sl_trans: Če jo bo našel, mislim, da moraš biti ti tisti, ki bo svetu sporočil, da je imel ta človek ves čas prav.

297.en_source: You want me to follow him into the city?
297.sl_trans: Želite, da mu sledim v mesto?

301.en_source: I've already made such a mess of everything.

304.sl_source: Lahko greš z menoj ali pa ne.
304.en_source: You can come with me or not.
304.sl_trans: Lahko greš z mano ali ne.

309.sl_trans: Zaradi tega smo videti bolj ameriški.

311.en_source: Just let me do the talking.

318.sl_source: To je ventilator, ki vodi v podzemne tunele.
318.en_source: It's a vent that leads to the subway tunnels underneath here.
318.sl_trans: To je odprtina, ki vodi v podzemne predore pod tem mestom.

319.sl_source: Pripeljati naju mora do 23.postaje na Manhattnu.
319.en_source: It should take us to the 23rd Street station in Manhattan.
319.sl_trans: Peljala naj bi nas do postaje na 23. ulici na Manhattnu.

320.en_source: You've got to be kidding me.

321.en_source: Aren't there rats and stuff down here?
321.sl_trans: Ali niso tu spodaj podgane in podobno?

322.en_source: I'm more concerned about lizards at this point.

323.sl_trans: Veliki, grdi, grdi, grdi, veliki kuščarji.

327.sl_source: Poročnik O'Neal nas je pravkar poklical.
327.en_source: Sergeant O'Neal just called down for us.
327.sl_trans: Seržant O'Neal nas je pravkar poklical.

328.en_source: He wants us to join him now, sir.
328.sl_trans: Želi, da se mu zdaj pridružimo, gospod.

344.en_source: How do we get down there?

346.en_source: How did they get down there?

348.en_source: You don't think they climbed down this thing?
348.sl_trans: Misliš, da niso splezali po tej stvari?

356.en_source: I guess we go this way.

357.en_source: Sir, we spotted him in section 5.
357.sl_trans: Gospod, opazili smo ga v oddelku 5.

359.sl_trans: Tarča se odpravi proti severu do oddelka 5.

360.sl_source: Ne streljajte, dokler ni mimo stavb v parku.
360.en_source: Do not fire until he has cleared the buildings and enters the park.
360.sl_trans: Ne streljajte, dokler ne zapusti stavb in vstopi v park.

361.en_source: Wait until he enters the park.

370.en_source: He's headed toward the Westside Highway.

372.en_source: The navy has something waiting for him.

373.sl_trans: Postaje s posadko za bojno postajo.

380.en_source: Torpedo room reports manned and ready.
380.sl_trans: Torpedna soba poroča o posadki in pripravljenosti.

391.en_source: We're locked on and closing in.

393.en_source: The target's heading right at us!

397.en_source: Stand by for impact in ten seconds.
397.sl_trans: Čakajte na udarec v desetih sekundah.

403.en_source: Prepare tubes 3 and 4 and lock on.
403.sl_trans: Pripravite cevi 3 in 4 ter ju zaklenite.

425.en_source: There's gotta be more than 20 eggs here.
425.sl_trans: Tu mora biti več kot 20 jajc.

443.en_source: I think we should leave now.
443.sl_trans: Mislim, da bi morali zdaj oditi.

444.en_source: I think that's a good idea.
444.sl_trans: Mislim, da je to dobra zamisel.

449.en_source: We have to keep them contained inside.

454.en_source: This is where the Knicks get showered and everything.
454.sl_trans: Tu se Knicksi oprhajo in vse ostalo.

456.sl_source: Stojim zraven Jerseyevega vhoda v Lincolnov tunel,... kjer je tisoče jeznih ubežnikov, ki hočejo nazaj v mesto.
456.en_source: I'm standing just outside the Jersey entrance to the Lincoln Tunnel... where thousands of angry refugees are demanding to be let back into the city.
456.sl_trans: Stojim tik pred vhodom v Lincolnov predor v Jerseyju, kjer na tisoče jeznih beguncev zahteva, da jih spustijo nazaj v mesto.

457.sl_source: Vse glavne ceste so zapolnjene z veselimi prebivalci Manhattna.
457.en_source: All major arteries into the city are clogged with jubilant Manhattanites.
457.sl_trans: Vse glavne prometnice v mesto so zamašene z radostnimi Manhattančani.

459.sl_source: Vašo pisarno so zasipali s klici.
459.en_source: Your office is swamped with calls.
459.sl_trans: Vaša pisarna je preplavljena s klici.

461.en_source: Do you have any idea what's going on out there?
461.sl_trans: Ali sploh veste, kaj se tam dogaja?

462.en_source: Phones are ringing off the hook.

463.en_source: People are screaming to be let back into the city.
463.sl_trans: Ljudje kričijo, da bi jih spustili nazaj v mesto.

464.sl_source: Pošiljamo potapljače, da bodo prinesli truplo.
464.en_source: We're sending divers in to retrieve the body.
464.sl_trans: Pošiljamo potapljače, ki bodo pobrali truplo.

466.en_source: Colonel, we've got to start a search for the nest.

467.sl_trans: S tem smo se že srečali.

468.sl_source: Kaj če je imel Nick prav in bomo vse zasrali?
468.en_source: What if Nick is right and we blow this whole thing?
468.sl_trans: Kaj pa, če ima Nick prav in bomo vse skupaj izpustili iz rok?

469.sl_source: To je edina možnost, da kaj napravimo.
469.en_source: This could be the only chance we have to do something about it.
469.sl_trans: To bi lahko bila edina priložnost, da nekaj storimo na tem področju.

471.sl_source: Hočem, da pregledate celo mesto, celo podzemno.
471.en_source: I want a sweep of the entire city and the subway.
471.sl_trans: Želim pregledati celotno mesto in podzemno železnico.

472.en_source: You don't have the authority to do that.

475.sl_source: Naj pošljejo bombnik, da podremo to stavbo.
475.en_source: Get them to send a bomber to blow up this building.
475.sl_trans: Naj pošljejo bombnika, ki bo razstrelil to stavbo.

478.en_source: Tell them it's a Code Dragonfly.
478.sl_trans: Povejte jim, da je to kodni zmajček.

483.en_source: All circuits are busy right now.

492.sl_source: Z mojimi možmi jih bomo ustavili.
492.en_source: My men and I will hold them here.
492.sl_trans: Moji možje in jaz jih bomo zadržali tukaj.

493.en_source: You'll have to go and get help.

495.sl_source: Le na en način lahko ugotoviva.
495.en_source: Only one way to find out.
495.sl_trans: To lahko ugotovite le na en način.

501.en_source: Why don't we go this way?
501.sl_trans: Zakaj ne bi šli po tej poti?

516.sl_source: Imate radio, walkie-talkie, karkoli za kontakt s svetom?
516.en_source: Do you have a radio, walkie-talkie, anything to contact the outside?
516.sl_trans: Ali imate radio, walkie-talkie, karkoli, s čimer bi lahko stopili v stik z zunanjim svetom?

518.en_source: It's no good. Circuits are jammed.

520.sl_source: Vem, kako bomo spravili sporočilo v svet.
520.en_source: I know how we can get a message to the outside.
520.sl_trans: Vem, kako lahko prenesemo sporočilo navzven.

525.en_source: The broadcast booth is over here.

527.sl_source: Naša TV postaja poroča s tekem Rangerjev.
527.en_source: Our network covers the Rangers games.

531.en_source: I was just about to get it.

532.en_source: The network is on an intranet.

533.en_source: It's a direct teed into our computer system.
533.sl_trans: To je neposredna povezava v naš računalniški sistem.

534.sl_source: Tudi postaja ne bo mogla do vojske.
534.en_source: Your station won't have an easier time reaching the military than I did.
534.sl_trans: Vaša postaja ne bo imela lažjega dostopa do vojske kot jaz.

535.en_source: Did they monitor all the news broadcasts?
535.sl_trans: Ali so spremljali vse informativne oddaje?

537.sl_trans: V redu, začenjamo z neposrednim prenosom.

538.en_source: We'll broadcast right from in here.

540.en_source: I'll try to get a message through.

541.sl_source: Ne pozabimo pri tem vračanju,... da bodo življenja spremenjena za vedno.
541.en_source: Let's not forget in our rush to return to the city... that many people have had their lives changed forever.
541.sl_trans: V naglici, da bi se vrnili v mesto, ne smemo pozabiti, da se je mnogim ljudem za vedno spremenilo življenje.

542.en_source: No one in the city has been untouched by the tragedy.
542.sl_trans: Tragedija ni prizadela nikogar v mestu.

543.en_source: The sick, the displaced, the injured--

544.en_source: There's no Ranger game on tonight.

545.sl_source: Če nas vidiš, nas lahko spraviš v oddajanje?
545.en_source: Ed, if you're seeing this, will you please put us on live?
545.sl_trans: Ed, če to vidiš, ali nas lahko vključiš v živo?

547.sl_source: Vem, da zveni bedasto, a moraš to storiti.
547.en_source: I know this sounds crazy, but you have to do it.
547.sl_trans: Vem, da se sliši noro, vendar morate to storiti.

549.en_source: I'm not putting you on live.
549.sl_trans: Ne bom vas vključil v neposredni prenos.

550.sl_source: Ne verjamem, da bo to storil.
550.en_source: I don't think he'll do it.
550.sl_trans: Mislim, da tega ne bo storil.

555.sl_source: Po celem mestu bodo, če jih ne uničimo.
555.en_source: They'll be all over the city if we don't stop them.
555.sl_trans: Če jih ne bomo ustavili, bodo po vsem mestu.

557.sl_source: Prišel je čas za vrnitev domov in nadaljevanje življenja.
557.en_source: The time has come to return to our homes and pick up our lives.
557.sl_trans: Prišel je čas, da se vrnemo na svoje domove in nadaljujemo s svojim življenjem.

560.sl_source: Po zaslugah naši pogumnih mož v uniformi--
560.en_source: Thanks to the heroic efforts of our boys in uniform--
560.sl_trans: Zaradi junaških prizadevanj naših fantov v uniformah...

564.sl_source: Javljamo se v živo iz Madison Square Gardna,..- kjer je dr. Niko Tatopoulos našel gnezdo pošasti.
564.en_source: We're live inside Madison Square Garden... where Dr. Niko Tatopoulos has discovered the beast's lair.
564.sl_trans: V živo smo v dvorani Madison Square Garden, kjer je doktor Niko Tatopoulos odkril brlog zveri.

565.sl_source: Doktor, nam lahko poveste, kaj se tukaj dogaja?
565.en_source: Doctor, can you tell us what's happening here?
565.sl_trans: Zdravnik, nam lahko poveste, kaj se tu dogaja?

569.sl_source: Torej, našli smo več kot 200 jajc-

571.sl_source: Pred nekaj trenutki so se začela izlegati.
571.en_source: Which a few moments ago began hatching.
571.sl_trans: Ki se je pred nekaj trenutki začel valiti.

572.sl_source: Male pošasti so velike tri metre in so se začele hranit.
572.en_source: The creatures just hatched are over nine feet tall, and they've begun feeding.
572.sl_trans: Pravkar izvaljena bitja so visoka več kot devet metrov in so se začela hraniti.

573.sl_source: Ko jim bo tukaj zmanjkalo hrane, bodo iskale novo izven gnezda.
573.en_source: When their food supply runs out here they will attempt to hunt down food of their own outside of this nest.
573.sl_trans: Ko jim tu zmanjka hrane, jo poskušajo uloviti zunaj tega gnezda.

575.sl_source: Če pridejo ven, se bodo reproducirale in imeli bomo novo vrsto,- ki nas bo zamenjala, kot dominantna na Zemlji.
575.en_source: If they get out, they'll multiply and soon a new species will emerge. One that could replace us as the dominant species of this planet.
575.sl_trans: Če se bodo razširile, se bodo razmnožile in kmalu bo nastala nova vrsta. Takšna, ki bi nas lahko nadomestila kot prevladujočo vrsto na tem planetu.

576.sl_source: Vsak od teh plazilcev, se izleže noseč.
576.en_source: Each one of these amazing reptiles... are born pregnant.
576.sl_trans: Vsak od teh neverjetnih plazilcev se rodi noseč.

577.sl_source: Teh 200 lahko postane 40000 v samo nekaj letih.
577.en_source: Adaptive and cunning, these 200 could become 40,000 within this year.
577.sl_trans: Prilagodljivih in zvitih 200 bi jih lahko v tem letu postalo 40.000.

578.sl_source: Če vojska posluša to obvestilo, mora čim prej uničiti to zgradbo še preden pošasti uidejo.-
578.en_source: If the military is listening to this broadcast... they have to destroy this building immediately... before these creatures can escape.
578.sl_trans: Če vojska posluša to oddajo, mora takoj uničiti to stavbo, preden ta bitja pobegnejo.

579.sl_source: Zaenkrat so vse ujete v dvorani,-- a ne bomo jih več mogli dolgo zadržati.-
579.en_source: So far they're all trapped inside this building... but I don't think we can contain them for long.
579.sl_trans: Zaenkrat so vsi ujeti v tej stavbi, vendar mislim, da jih ne bomo mogli dolgo zadrževati.

580.sl_source: So zelo močne, energične..- in iščejo hrano.
580.en_source: They're very strong, agile... and they're looking for food.
580.sl_trans: So zelo močni, okretni in iščejo hrano.

581.sl_source: Vaša teorija o gnezdu je naposled pravilna.
581.en_source: So your theory of the creature nesting turned out to be correct after all.
581.sl_trans: Torej se je vaša teorija o gnezdenju bitij vendarle izkazala za pravilno.

582.sl_source: Ne glede, kaj se zgodi z nami, najpomembneje je,... da uničite to zgradbo, še preden lahko pobegnejo.
582.en_source: Regardless of what happens to us, the most important thing... is that this building be destroyed immediately before they escape.
582.sl_trans: Ne glede na to, kaj se bo zgodilo z nami, je najpomembneje, da to stavbo uničimo takoj, preden pobegnejo.

583.sl_source: Poročamo "v živo" iz Madison Square Gardna... za vas Audrey Timmonds, WIDF News.
583.en_source: Reporting live from Madison Square Garden... this is Audrey Timmonds for WIDF News.
583.sl_trans: V živo iz Madison Square Gardena poroča Audrey Timmonds za WIDF News.

587.en_source: Let me spell it out for you.

588.sl_source: Hočem, da razstrelite Madison Square Garden.
588.en_source: I want you to blow up Madison Square Garden.
588.sl_trans: Želim, da razstreliš Madison Square Garden.

589.sl_source: Dobra novica je, da so slišali opozorilo.
589.en_source: The good news is they got that message.
589.sl_trans: Dobra novica je, da so prejeli to sporočilo.

590.sl_source: Slaba novica, imamo le šest minut za pobeg.
590.en_source: The bad news is we've got less than six minutes to get out.
590.sl_trans: Slaba novica je, da imamo manj kot šest minut časa, da odidemo.

594.en_source: Where did you find this guy?

611.sl_source: Stallion 1-5 kaže laserski pregled nad Gardnom.
611.en_source: Stallion 1-5 showing a good laser track on top of the Garden.
611.sl_trans: Žrebec 1-5 kaže dobro lasersko sled na vrhu vrta.

613.en_source: How much time do we have left?
613.sl_trans: Koliko časa imamo še na voljo?

620.sl_trans: Je z vami vse v redu?

622.sl_source: Nisem si mislila, da je tvoje življenje tako zanimivo.
622.en_source: Somehow I never thought your life was this exciting.
622.sl_trans: Nikoli nisem mislil, da je tvoje življenje tako razburljivo.

630.en_source: Running would be a good idea.

635.en_source: You better step on it, Mr. French.

636.sl_source: Pojdite po 57. ulici in prečkajte Westside.
636.en_source: Take 57th Street and cut up the Westside.
636.sl_trans: Zapeljite se po 57. ulici in prečkajte Westside.

652.sl_trans: Je z vsemi vse v redu?

653.sl_trans: Je z vsemi vse v redu?

663.sl_source: Poročnik Rodgers, so F-18 še vedno v zraku?
663.en_source: Lieutenant Rodgers, are those F-18s still in the air?
663.sl_trans: Poročnik Rodgers, ali so letala F-18 še vedno v zraku?

669.sl_source: Vsako TAXI podjetje ima zabeležene... radio frekvence svojih avtomobilov.
669.en_source: Every cab company keeps a record... of each of its cab's radio frequencies.
669.sl_trans: Vsako taksi podjetje vodi evidenco radijskih frekvenc vsake svoje kabine.

672.en_source: In there. Go in the tunnel.

674.en_source: Now where would you like to go?

678.en_source: Nice trick with the cab I.D.

681.en_source: We're in the-- Park Avenue Tunnel.

682.en_source: He's got us trapped in here.
682.sl_trans: Tu nas je ujel v past.

683.sl_source: Speljati jo morate na čistino,... da jo bomo lahko sestrelili-
683.en_source: You guys have got to lure him out into the open... so we can get a clear shot at him.
683.sl_trans: Morate ga zvabiti na prosto, da ga bomo lahko dobro videli.

685.en_source: You want us to wash him up, too?

689.en_source: How would you like us to do that?

692.sl_source: Odpravil se je proti Brooklynskemu mostu.
692.en_source: He's headed toward the Brooklyn Bridge.

693.sl_source: Tarča se giblje proti Brooklynskemu mostu.
693.en_source: Target is heading toward the Brooklyn Bridge, sir.
693.sl_trans: Cilj je usmerjen proti Brooklynskemu mostu, gospod.

694.en_source: Direct the F-18s to the Brooklyn Bridge.
694.sl_trans: Usmerite letala F-18 na Brooklynski most.

697.sl_trans: To se ti zdi, da se šališ.

700.en_source: You're goin' the wrong way, man!

707.en_source: He's caught in the suspension cables.
707.sl_trans: Ujel se je v viseče kable.

710.en_source: Stallion 1-5, tally one on the bridge.

714.sl_source: Zadetek, a tarča se še premika.
714.en_source: Direct hit, but the target is still moving.
714.sl_trans: Neposreden zadetek, vendar se tarča še vedno premika.

725.en_source: I don't think we should exploit this.
725.sl_trans: Mislim, da tega ne bi smeli izkoriščati.

728.en_source: I do the thinking around here.

730.sl_source: Veste, kaj mislim o vas in vaši kampanji?
730.en_source: You know what I think about you and your campaign?
730.sl_trans: Veste, kaj si mislim o vas in vaši kampanji?

734.en_source: That is one hell of a job, soldier.
734.sl_trans: To je prekleto dobro delo, vojak.

735.en_source: That's one hell of a job.

737.sl_source: Zgodbo sem že obljubil eni drugi novinarki.
737.en_source: I've already promised my story... as an exclusive to another reporter.
737.sl_trans: Svojo zgodbo sem že obljubil... ekskluzivno drugemu novinarju.

746.en_source: All right, folks, let's keep it movin'.

747.sl_source: Si ti vzela kaseto iz kamere?
747.en_source: You take the tape out of the camera?

749.en_source: I couldn't have just lost it.
749.sl_trans: Nisem ga mogel kar tako izgubiti.

755.sl_source: Povejte prijatelju, da bom vrnil kaseto, ko bom jo malo obdelal.
755.en_source: Tell your friends I will send the tape after I've removed a few items from it.
755.sl_trans: Prijateljem povejte, da bom trak poslal, ko bom z njega odstranil nekaj predmetov.

757.en_source: I wanted to say au revoir.

758.en_source: Thank you for your help, my friend.

761.sl_source: Kdo je sploh bil ta Francoz?
761.en_source: Who was that French guy anyway?

762.sl_trans: Samo nekdo, ki se ukvarja z zavarovalništvom.

763.sl_source: Je rekel kaj o moji kaseti?
763.en_source: Did he say anything about my tape?
763.sl_trans: Je kaj rekel o mojem traku?

764.en_source: Yeah, he said something about your tape.
764.sl_trans: Ja, rekel je nekaj o tvojem traku.

765.en_source: Does he have my tape or not?
765.sl_trans: Ali ima moj trak ali ne?
